-- Western Union suspends services with Russia's Bank Rossiya
-- 
-- Fri Mar 21, 2014 03:00PM EDT
-- None



LONDON, March 21 (Reuters) - The world's largest money transfer company Western Union <WU.N> said on Friday it has suspended its services for Russia's Bank Rossiya.

In a statement, Western Union said its money transfer service continues to be available at its 20,000 plus locations and self-service terminals across Russia. Earlier on Friday Bank Rossiya said Visa Inc <V.N> and MasterCard Inc <MA.N> had stopped providing services for payment transactions for its clients. [ID:nL6N0MI0VJ]